<eesti>N&otilde;uded veovahendile </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for Means of Transport </inglise>
<eesti>Teede- ja sideministri 14. novembri 2000. a m&auml;&auml;rus nr 89 </eesti>
<inglise>Regulation No. 89 of the Minister of Transport and Communications of 14 November 2000 </inglise>
<eesti>(RTL 2000, 120, 1879), </eesti>
<inglise>(RTL (1) 2000, 120, 1879), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 26. novembril 2000. a. </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 26 November 2000. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;rus kehtestatakse "Kemikaaliseaduse" (RT I 1998, 47, 697; 1999, 45, 512) paragrahvi 11 l&otilde;ike 3 punkti 2 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>This Regulation is established pursuant to clause 11 (3) 2) of the "Chemicals Act" (RT (2) I 1998, 47, 697; 1999, 45, 512). </inglise>
<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldn&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>General requirements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus kehtestab n&otilde;uded Eestis registreeritud veovahendile ja Eestit k&uuml;lastavale v&auml;lisriigi veovahendile inimese tervist, keskkonda v&otilde;i vara ohustada v&otilde;iva kemikaali, seda sisaldava toote v&otilde;i materjali veol. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Regulation establishes requirements which apply to means of transport registered in Estonia and to foreign means of transport visiting Estonia which carry chemicals that may endanger human health, environment or property, or products and materials which contain such chemicals. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Veovahend peab olema tehniliselt korras ja tagama ohutuse veol, kui kemikaal v&otilde;i seda sisaldav toode v&otilde;i materjal on klassifitseeritud kuuluvaks &uuml;hte allj&auml;rgnevasse ohuklassi: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Means of transport shall be in good technical condition and ensure safety upon the carriage of chemicals or materials which contain chemicals, if the chemicals or materials belong to one of the following hazard divisions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ohuklass 1 - l&otilde;hkematerjalid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) hazard division 1: explosive substances; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ohuklass 2 - r&otilde;hu all olevad, r&otilde;hu all v&otilde;i madalal temperatuuril veeldatud v&otilde;i r&otilde;hu all lahustatud gaasid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) hazard division 2: gases under pressure, gases which have been liquefied under pressure or at a low temperature, and gases which have been dissolved under pressure; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ohuklass 3 - tuleohtlikud vedelikud leekpunktiga mitte &uuml;le 61 &deg;C v&otilde;i leekpunkti temperatuuril v&otilde;i k&otilde;rgemal veetavad vedelikud; </eesti>
<inglise>3) hazard division 3: flammable liquids with a flash point of not more than 61&deg;C, and liquids which are carried at a temperature which is equal or higher than its flash point; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ohuklass 4.1 - tuleohtlikud tahksed, iseeneslikult reageerivad ained v&otilde;i desensibiliseeritud l&otilde;hkeained; </eesti>
<inglise>4) hazard division 4.1: flammable solids liable to spontaneous reaction and desensitized explosives; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ohuklass 4.2 - ises&uuml;ttivad ained; </eesti>
<inglise>5) hazard division 4.2: substances liable to spontaneous combustion; </inglise>
<eesti>6) ohuklass 4.3 - kokkupuutel veega tuleohtlikku gaasi eraldavad ained; </eesti>
<inglise>6) hazard division 4.3: substances which in contact with water emit flammable gases; </inglise>
<eesti>7) ohuklass 5.1 - oks&uuml;deerivad ained; </eesti>
<inglise>7) hazard division 5.1: oxydizing agents; </inglise>
<eesti>8) ohuklass 5.2 - orgaanilised peroksiidid; </eesti>
<inglise>8) hazard division 5.2: organic peroxides; </inglise>
<eesti>9) ohuklass 6.1 - m&uuml;rgised ained; </eesti>
<inglise>9) hazard division 6.1: toxic substances; </inglise>
<eesti>10) ohuklass 6.2 - nakkusohtlikud materjalid; </eesti>
<inglise>10) hazard division 6.2: infectious materials; </inglise>
<eesti>11) ohuklass 7 - radioaktiivsed materjalid; </eesti>
<inglise>11) hazard division 7: radioactive materials; </inglise>
<eesti>12) ohuklass 8 - s&ouml;&ouml;bivad ained; </eesti>
<inglise>12) hazard division 8: corrosive substances; </inglise>
<eesti>13) ohuklass 9 - ained, millest tulenevad ohud ei ole kaetud eelmiste ohuklassidega. </eesti>
<inglise>13) hazard division 9: substances posing dangers which are not included in the previous hazard divisions. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uded laevale </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for Ships </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uded ohtliku veose veol pakendis ja mahtlastina </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for carriage of dangerous goods in packages and in bulk </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laev peab sobima oma ehituse, seadmete, varustuse ja meeskonna ettevalmistuse poolest ohtliku veose mereveoks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The construction, equipment, facilities of a ship, and the training of its crew shall be suitable for the maritime carriage of dangerous goods. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Laev kogumahutavusega 500 ja suurem, mis on ehitatud 1. septembril 1984. a v&otilde;i hiljem, v&otilde;i kogumahutavusega kuni 500 ja on ehitatud 1. veebruaril 1992. a v&otilde;i hiljem, peab omama SOLAS 74 peat&uuml;ki II-2 reegli 54 alusel v&auml;lja antud kehtivat tunnistust laeva vastavusest ohtlike kaupade mereveo erin&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Ships with a gross tonnage of 500 or more which have been built not earlier than on 1 September 1984, and ships with a gross tonnage of up to 500 which have been built not earlier than on 1 February 1992 shall have a valid certificate issued in proof of compliance of the ship with the special requirements for maritime carriage of dangerous goods, issued on the basis of rule 52 of Chapter II-2 of SOLAS. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Pakendis veol peab ohtliku veose stoovima ja segregeerima teistest veostest nii, nagu s&auml;testab rahvusvaheline ohtlike kaupade mereveo eeskiri (International Maritime Dangerous Goods Code) (IMDG koodeks) ja puistlastina veol nii, nagu s&auml;testab tahkete puistekaupade veo ohutuseeskiri (Code of Safe Practice for Solid Bulk Cargoes) (BC koodeks), kuid mitte vastuolus eelmises l&otilde;ikes mainitud tunnistuse s&auml;tetega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Dangerous goods carried in packages shall be stowed and segregated from other cargo pursuant to the provisions of the International Maritime Dangerous Goods Code (IMDG Code) and dangerous goods carried as solid bulk cargoes shall be stowed and segregated from other cargo pursuant to the provisions of the Code of Safe Practice for Solid Bulk Cargoes (BC Code), but not contrary to the provisions of the certificate specified in the previous subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>Alates 1. jaanuarist 2001. a peab pakitud ohtlike veoste merevedu toimuma IMDG koodeksi versiooni 30-00 (Amendments 30-00) s&auml;tete kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>As of 1 January 2001, maritime carriage of packaged dangerous goods shall be conducted pursuant to Amendments 30-00 of the IMDG Code. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kiirlaevas, kus on &uuml;le 12 reisija, ei ole lubatud vedada ohtlikku veost. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Dangerous goods shall not be carried by high speed craft with more than twelve passengers on board. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Laevas ohtlike veoste t&otilde;stmiseks kasutatav kaubat&otilde;stuk peab olema kord viie aasta jooksul katsetatud ja l&auml;binud iga-aastase &uuml;levaatuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The goods lift used for the lifting of dangerous goods on board a ship shall be tested once during every five years and shall pass an annual survey. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Ammooniumnitraati v&otilde;i mineraalv&auml;etist, mis sisaldab &uuml;le 40% ammooniumnitraati ammoonium- ja nitraatioonide st&ouml;hhiomeetrilise summana, on lubatud vedada laeva A-kategooria masinaruumiga piirnevas lastiruumis, kui piirde tulekindlus vastab SOLAS 74 kategooria A-60 n&otilde;uetele, v&otilde;i ammooniumnitraat tuleb paigutada v&auml;hemalt 3 m kaugusele sellest piirdest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) It is permitted to carry ammonium nitrate and mineral fertilisers which contain over 40% of ammonium nitrate calculated as the stoichiometric sum of ammonium and nitrate ions in the ship's hold adjacent to the category A engine room, if the flame resistance of the peripheral structure between the two rooms is in compliance with the requirements of category A-60 of SOLAS 74, or if the ammonium nitrate is placed at least 3 meters away from the peripheral structure. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Plaskudes on lubatud vedada kasutatud tuumak&uuml;tust, plutooniumi ja k&otilde;rgradioaktiivseid j&auml;&auml;tmeid vastavalt laeva INF klassile, mille m&auml;&auml;ramise aluseks on Rahvusvahelise Mereorganisatsiooni eeskiri plaskudes oleva kasutatud tuumak&uuml;tuse, plutooniumi ja k&otilde;rgradioaktiivsete j&auml;&auml;tmete ohutuks veoks laeval (Code for Safe Carriage of Irradiated Nuclear Fuel, Plutonium and High-Level Radioactive Wastes in Flasks on Board Ship). (8) Veeteede Ameti, L&auml;ti Mereadministratsiooni, Poola Majandusministeeriumi, Rootsi Mereadministratsiooni, Saksamaa Liikluse, Ehituse- ja Elamumajanduse Liiduministeeriumi, Soome Mereadministratsiooni ja Taani Mereadministratsiooni vahel s&otilde;lmitud vastastikuse m&otilde;istmise memorandum ohtlike kaupade veoks parvlaevadega vastavalt "Rahvusvahelise ohtlike kaupade mereveo koodeksile", "Rahvusvahelisele ohtlike kaupade raudteevedude korrale" ja "Rahvusvahelisele ohtlike kaupade autoveo Euroopa kokkuleppele" (L&auml;&auml;nemeremaade kokkulepe) on rakendatav ohtliku veose veol, kui parvlaevale on v&auml;lja antud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 mainitud tunnistus v&otilde;i on see tunnistus v&auml;lja antud L&auml;&auml;nemeremaade kokkuleppe paragrahvi 7 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The carriage of irradiated nuclear fuel, plutonium and high-level radioactive wastes in flasks on board ships shall be performed according to the INF classification of the ship which is determined according to the Code for Safe Carriage of Irradiated Nuclear Fuel, Plutonium and High-Level Radioactive Wastes in Flasks on Board Ship of the International Maritime Organisation. (8) The Memorandum of Understanding on Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Ferryboat pursuant to the International Code of Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Sea, the Regulations Concerning the International Carriage of dangerous Goods by Rail and the Agreement Concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road entered into between the Maritime Board and the Maritime Administration of Latvia, the Ministry of Economic Affairs of Poland, the Maritime Administration of Sweden, the Federal Ministry for Traffic, Building and Housing of Germany, the Maritime Administration of Finland and the Maritime Administration of Denmark (the Baltic Agreement) shall be applied upon the carriage of dangerous goods by ferryboat, if the ferryboat has been issued the certificate specified in subsection (2) of this section, or if such certificate is issued on the basis of section 7 of the Baltic Agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Gaasitanker </eesti>
<inglise>Gas carrier </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laev, mis on ehitatud ja varustatud seadmetega veeldatud gaasi veoks mahtlastina (gaasitanker), v&otilde;ib vedada gaasi mahtlastina, kui tunnistuse laeva k&otilde;lblikkusest veeldatud gaasi veoks mahtlastina v&auml;ljaandmise aluseks on: 1) rahvusvaheline veeldatud gaasi vedellastina vedava laeva ehituse ja seadmete eeskiri (International Code for the Construction and Equipment of Ships Carrying Liquefied Gases in Bulk) (IGC koodeks) v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A ship which has been built and is equipped for the carriage of liquefied gases in bulk (gas carrier) may be used for the carriage of liquefied gases in bulk if the ship has been issued a certificate of suitability for carriage of liquefied gases in bulk on the basis of: 1) the International Code for the Construction and Equipment of Ships Carrying Liquefied Gases in Bulk (IGC Code) or </inglise>
<eesti>2) veeldatud gaasi vedava laeva ehituse ja seadmete eeskiri (Code for the Construction and Equipment of Ships Carrying Liquefied Gases in Bulk) (GC koodeks), kui laev on ehitatud enne 1. juulit 1986. a. </eesti>
<inglise>2) Code for the Construction and Equipment of Ships Carrying Liquefied Gases in Bulk (GC Code), if the ship has been built earlier than 1 July 1986. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eelmises l&otilde;ikes mainitud tunnistuse kohustuslik lisa on veoks lubatud kemikaalide nimekiri koos s&auml;testatud veotingimustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The certificate specified in the previous subsection shall have a mandatory appendix which sets out a list of chemicals the carriage of which is permitted and provides the carriage conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Gaasitankeriks &uuml;mber ehitatud laeva ehitamise ajaks tuleb lugeda &uuml;mberehitamise aeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A gas carrier converted from other types of ship is deemed to be built at the time of the reconstruction of the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Gaasitanker peab p&auml;rast remonti, modifitseerimist ja nende t&ouml;&ouml;dega kaasnenud muudatusi seadmete ja varustuse osas vastama v&auml;hemalt n&otilde;udmistele, mis olid rakendatavad enne mainitud t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemise algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A gas carrier which is repaired or modified with alterations made to its equipment and facilities shall, as a minimum, conform to the requirements which were applicable to the carrier before the beginning of the aforementioned work. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui enne 1. juulit 1986. a ehitatud gaasitankerit on p&auml;rast seda kuup&auml;eva remonditud v&otilde;i modifitseeritud ja sellega on kaasnenud olulised &uuml;mberehitused v&otilde;i on muudetud oluliselt gaasitankeri seadmeid v&otilde;i varustust, siis peavad tehtud muudatused olema vastavuses IGC koodeksi n&otilde;uetega. </eesti>
<inglise>If a gas carrier built before 1 July 1986 has been repaired or modified after such date with material reconstruction of or alterations made to its equipment and facilities then the reconstruction and alterations made must conform to the IGC Code. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Kemikaalitanker </eesti>
<inglise>Chemical tanker </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laev, mis on ehitatud ja varustatud seadmetega kemikaali veoks mahtlastina, v&otilde;i naftatanker, mis veab muud kemikaali kui nafta v&otilde;i naftasaadus (kemikaalitanker), v&otilde;ib vedada kemikaali mahtlastina, kui tunnistuse laeva k&otilde;lblikkusest kemikaali veoks mahtlastina v&auml;ljaandmise aluseks on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A ship which has been built and is equipped for the carriage of chemicals in bulk, or an oil tanker carrying other chemicals than oil or oil products (chemical tanker) may be used for the carriage of chemicals in bulk is the ship has been issued a certificate of suitability for carriage of chemicals in bulk on the basis of: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rahvusvaheline ohtlikku kemikaali mahtlastina vedava laeva ehituse ja seadmete eeskiri (International Code for the Construction and Equipment of Ships Carrying Dangerous Chemicals in Bulk) (IBC koodeks); </eesti>
<inglise>1) the International Code for the Construction and Equipment of Ships Carrying Dangerous Chemicals in Bulk (IBC Code); 2) the Code for the Construction and Equipment of Ships Carrying Dangerous Chemicals in Bulk (BCH Code), if the ship has been built earlier than 1 July 1986. </inglise>
<eesti>2) ohtlikku kemikaali mahtlastina vedava laeva ehituse ja seadmete eeskiri (Code for the Construction and Equipment of Ships Carrying Dangerous Chemicals in Bulk) (BCH koodeks), kui laev on ehitatud enne 1. juulit 1986. a. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The certificate specified in the previous subsection shall have a mandatory appendix which sets out a list of chemicals the carriage of which is permitted and provides the carriage conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eelmises l&otilde;ikes nimetatud tunnistuse kohustuslik lisa on veoks lubatud kemikaalide nimekiri koos s&auml;testatud veotingimustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) It is permitted to carry the following chemicals in the cargo tank: </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lastitankis on lubatud vedada: 1) MARPOL 73/78 II lisas m&auml;&auml;ratletud reostuskategooria B kemikaali, kui tanki t&uuml;hjenduss&uuml;steem katsetamisel ei j&auml;ta tankist v&auml;lja pumpamata enne 1. juulit 1986. a ehitatud kemikaalitankeris &uuml;le 0,3 m (3) ja 1. juulil 1986. a v&otilde;i hiljem ehitatud kemikaalitankeris &uuml;le 0,1 m (3); </eesti>
<inglise>1) pollution category B chemicals determined in Appendix II to MARPOL 73/78, if upon the testing of the discharge system of a chemical tanker built earlier than 1 July 1986, less than 0,3 m (3) of liquid remains in the tank after pumping the tank out; in the case of chemical tankers built on 1 July 1986 or later, less than 1,3 m (3) of remaining liquid is allowed; </inglise>
<eesti>2) reostuskategooria C kemikaali, kui tanki t&uuml;hjenduss&uuml;steem katsetamisel ei j&auml;ta tankist v&auml;lja pumpamata enne 1. juulit 1986. a ehitatud kemikaalitankeris &uuml;le 0,9 m (3) ja 1. juulil 1986. a v&otilde;i hiljem ehitatud kemikaalitankeris &uuml;le 0,3 m (3). </eesti>
<inglise>2) pollution category C chemicals, if upon the testing of the discharge system of a chemical tanker built earlier than 1 July 1986, less than 0,9 m (3) of liquid remains in the tank after pumping the tank out; in the case of chemical tankers built on 1 July 1986 or later, less than 0,3 m (3) of remaining liquid is allowed. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kemikaalitankeriks &uuml;mber ehitatud laeva ehitamise ajaks tuleb lugeda &uuml;mberehitamise aeg, v&auml;lja arvatud juhud, kui enne 1. juulit 1986. a ehitatud laevale on l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tunnistus v&auml;lja antud BCH koodeksi alusel v&otilde;i kemikaalitankeriga on lubatud vedada ohtlikest kemikaalidest ainult keskkonnaohtlikke kemikaale. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A chemical tanker converted from other types of ship is deemed to be built at the time of the reconstruction of the ship, except in the cases where a ship built earlier than on 1 July 1986 has been issued the certificate specified in subsection (1) on the basis of the BCH Code, or if no dangerous chemicals except environmentally dangerous chemicals are permitted to be carried on board of the tanker. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kemikaalitanker peab p&auml;rast remonti, modifitseerimist ja nende t&ouml;&ouml;dega kaasnenud muudatusi seadmete ja varustuse osas vastama v&auml;hemalt n&otilde;udmistele, mis olid rakendatavad enne mainitud t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemise algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A chemical tanker which is repaired or modified with alterations made to its equipment and facilities shall, as a minimum, conform to the requirements applicable before the beginning of the aforementioned work. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui enne 1. juulit 1986. a ehitatud kemikaalitankerit on p&auml;rast seda kuup&auml;eva remonditud v&otilde;i modifitseeritud ja sellega on kaasnenud olulised &uuml;mberehitused v&otilde;i on muudetud oluliselt kemikaalitankeri seadmeid v&otilde;i varustust, siis peavad tehtud muudatused olema vastavuses IBC koodeksi n&otilde;uetega. </eesti>
<inglise>If a chemical tanker built before 1 July 1986 has been repaired or modified after such date with material reconstruction of or alterations made to its equipment and facilities then the reconstruction and alterations made must conform to the IBC Code. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Laeva, mis ei ole kemikaalitanker, on lubatud kasutada IBC koodeksi peat&uuml;ki 17 nimekirjas olevate reostuskategooria D ja peat&uuml;ki 18 nimekirjas olevate kemikaalide veoks, kui on olemas kehtiv tunnistus laeva vastavusest MARPOL 73/78 II lisa n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Ships which are not chemical tankers may be used for the carriage of pollution category D chemicals listed in Chapter 17 and of chemicals listed in Chapter 18 of the IBC Code if the ship has been issued a valid certificate of compliance with the requirements of Appendix II to MARPOL 73/78. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Naftatanker </eesti>
<inglise>Oil tanker </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Laev, mis on ehitatud ja varustatud seadmetega nafta ja naftasaaduste veoks mahtlastina, v&otilde;i kemikaalitanker, mis v&otilde;ib vedada naftat v&otilde;i naftasaadust mahtlastina (naftatanker), peab oma ehituse ja seadmetega varustatuse osas vastama MARPOL 73/78 I lisa n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A ship which has been built and is equipped for the carriage of oil or oil products in bulk, or a chemical tanker which has permission to carry oil or oil products in bulk (oil tanker) shall conform to the requirements of Annex I of MARPOL 73/78. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Mahtlasti leekpunktiga kuni 61 &deg;C on lubatud vedada, kui naftatankeril rakendatavad meetmed tuleohutuse tagamiseks vastavad v&auml;hemalt SOLAS 74 peat&uuml;ki II-2 osa D n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An oil tanker may be used for the carriage of bulk cargo with a flash point of up to 61&deg;C if the measures to ensure fire safety on board the tanker conform, as a minimum, to the requirements of part D, chapter II-2 of SOLAS 74. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uded mootors&otilde;idukile ja haagisele </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for Motor Vehicles and Trailers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;iduki ja haagise tehnoseisund </eesti>
<inglise>Roadworthiness of motor vehicles and trailers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Mootors&otilde;iduki ja haagise (veok) &uuml;ldine tehnoseisund peab vastama teede- ja sideministri 29. mai 1998. a m&auml;&auml;rusega nr 21 (RTL 1998, 278-286, 1169 ja 1170; 1999, 52, 697; 90, 1100; 2000, 5, 31) kinnitatud "S&otilde;iduki tehnoj&auml;relevalve eeskirja" ja ohtlike veoste veo korral teede- ja sideministri 15. jaanuari 1996. a m&auml;&auml;rusega nr 3 (RTL 1996, 43-45, 292; 139, 687; 1997, 90, 530; 1999, 77, 958; 2000, 108, 1656) kinnitatud "Ohtlike veoste riigisisese autoveo eeskirja" n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The general state of roadworthiness of motor vehicles and trailers (means of transport) shall conform to the requirements established in the "Technical Surveillance Rules for Vehicles" approved by Regulation No. 21 of the Minister of Transport and Communications of 29 May 1998 (RTL 1998, 278-286, 1169 and 1170; 1999, 52, 697; 90, 1100; 2000, 5, 31), and in the case of the carriage of dangerous goods, to the requirements established in the "Rules for Internal Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road" approved by Regulation No. </inglise>

<eesti>(2) Veokile paigutatud lisa k&uuml;tusepaak peab vastama "S&otilde;iduki tehnoj&auml;relevalve eeskirja" lisa 1 koodi 703 n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An additional fuel tank installed on a means of transport shall conform to the requirements of code 701 of Annex 1 to the "Technical Surveillance Rules for Vehicles". </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Veokile esitatavad n&otilde;uded parvlaeval </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for vehicles on board of ferryboat </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Veokil peab olema kummalgi k&uuml;ljel piisav arv kinnituskohti, mis kannavad kinnitusj&otilde;u otse veoki kandvale osale v&otilde;i raamile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A means of transport shall have an adequate number of securing points at both of its sides which should be capable of transferring the forces from the lashings to the chassis of the means of transport. </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud on kinnituskohana kasutada l&ouml;&ouml;gineelajat v&otilde;i mis tahes telge, kui selle konstruktsioon ei taga kinnitusj&otilde;u otsest &uuml;lekandmist veoki kandvale osale v&otilde;i raamile. </eesti>
<inglise>Bumpers or axles which are not constructed in a manner which ensures that the forces from the lashings are transferred to the chassis of the means of transport shall not be used as securing points. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kinnituskoht peab veokil olema selgesti n&auml;htavalt t&auml;histatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The securing points shall be clearly marked on a means of transport. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kinnituskoha ava v&auml;ikseim l&auml;bim&otilde;&otilde;t s&otilde;ltumata kujust peab olema v&auml;hemalt 80 mm. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The diameter of a securing point at its narrowest point shall not be less than 80 mm regardless of the shape of the securing point. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) V&auml;him lubatud j&otilde;ud, mida kinnituskoht peab ilma j&auml;&auml;vdeformatsioonita vastu v&otilde;tma, leitakse lisas toodud tabelist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The minimum authorised force that a securing point must endure without permanent deformation thereof shall be found in the table set out in the Annex. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Haagisega mootors&otilde;iduki korral peab olema v&otilde;imalik eraldi kinnitada mootors&otilde;idukit ja iga haagist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The securing points of a motor vehicle with trailers shall ensure the possibility to secure the vehicle and each trailer separately. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Sadulveoki korral piisab veoki esiosas kahest kinnituskohast, kui nende paigutus ja tugevusvaru v&otilde;imaldavad v&auml;ltida kinnitatud veoki esiosa k&uuml;lgnihkumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A fifth-wheel tractor may have only two securing points in the front part of the means of transport if the location and strength of the securing points is sufficient to prevent lateral movement of the front part of the means of transport. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Laeva on lubatud v&otilde;tta veokit, mille toites&uuml;steem v&otilde;i veos ei leki ja koorem on veokile kinnitatud merekindlalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) In order to be allowed on board of a ship, the fuel system of a means of transport must not leak and its cargo must be secured in a manner appropriate for carriage by sea. </inglise>
