<inglise>Requirements for Rail Vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Ohtlike kaupade vedu raudteel </eesti>
<inglise>Carriage of dangerous goods by rail </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ohtlike kaupade raudteeveol kohaldatakse "Rahvusvahelise raudteekaubaveo kokkuleppe" (RRKK/SMGS) lisa 2 "Ohtlike kaupade veo eeskiri" (j&otilde;ustus 1. m&auml;rtsil 1993. a teede- ja sideministri 15. jaanuari 1993. a m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 1 alusel) s&auml;tteid ning SR&Uuml; riikide, L&auml;ti Vabariigi, Leedu Vabariigi ja Eesti Vabariigi raudtee administratsioonide n&otilde;ukogu poolt vastu v&otilde;etud kokkuleppeid SMGS-i &uuml;ksikute s&auml;tete kohaldamise kohta rahvusvahelises raudteeotse&uuml;henduses SR&Uuml; ja Balti riikide vahel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the carriage of dangerous goods by rail, the provisions of Annex 2 "Rules for Carriage of Dangerous Goods" of the "Agreement on International Carriage of Goods by Rail" (RRKK/SMGS) (entered into force 1 March 1993 on the basis of Regulation No.1 of the Minister of Transport and Communications of 15 January 1993) and the agreements concerning the application of certain provisions of the SMGS in international direct rail connection between the CIS and the Baltic States entered into between the CIS, the Republic of Latvia, the Republic of Lithuania and the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rongiliiklus ja man&ouml;&ouml;vrit&ouml;&ouml; ohtliku veosega on s&auml;testatud "Raudtee rongiliikluse ja man&ouml;&ouml;vrit&ouml;&ouml; juhendis", mis on vastu v&otilde;etud teede- ja sideministri 13. aprilli 2000. a m&auml;&auml;rusega nr 22 (RTL 2000, 54, 836). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Railway train traffic and shunting upon the carriage of dangerous loads is provided for in the "Guidelines for Railway Train Traffic and Shunting" approved by Regulation No. 22 of the Minister of Transport and Communications of 13 April 2000 (RTL 2000, 54,836). </inglise>


